A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Sergeant (Ret.) Mary L. Clements; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Sergeant (Ret.) Mary L. Clements served as a guardian of this nation's freedom
3 and liberty with the United States Army, valiantly protecting and supporting her fellow
4 Americans throughout her distinguished military career; and
5 WHEREAS, a native of Eatonton, Georgia, she became the first in her family to earn a high
6 school diploma, attend and graduate from college, and enlist in the military, excelling both
7 academically and athletically by earning three full academic and athletic scholarships before
8 choosing to enlist in December 1981; and
9 WHEREAS, she was awarded the Army Commendation Medal for creating a mailroom and
10 constructing a secure storage area for body bags during Operation Desert Storm and
11 Operation Desert Shield, both of which greatly increased morale within the command; and
12 WHEREAS, after her military service, she earned a Bachelor of Science in psychology and
13 an Associate of Science in physical education, receiving recognition from Who's Who
14 Among Students in American Universities and Colleges while also accumulating over 1,000
15 hours of volunteer service; and
