16 WHEREAS, she has dedicated over 30 years to mentoring and youth programs as a Girl
17 Scout leader, coach, referee, Junior Achievement leader, and developer of mentorship and
18 physical fitness programs for at-risk youth; and
19 WHEREAS, she remains an active and committed advocate for veterans as Vice President
20 and Historian of the Atlanta Metro Chapter of the National Association of Black Military
21 Women, a lifetime member of the Disabled American Veterans and Veterans of Foreign
22 Wars, and a chartered member of the Women's Memorial; and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
24 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
26 recognize and commend Sergeant (Ret.) Mary L. Clements for her exceptional military
27 service, community leadership, and lifelong dedication to uplifting others as well as extend
28 the most sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
30 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Sergeant (Ret.)
31 Mary L. Clements.
